    "poemName": "A doctor of Schizophrenia",
    "poemAuthor": "Zekiah",
    "poemContent": {
        "type": "fragment",
        "styles": [],
        "children": [
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Bland, fluorescent lighting, "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "the door's full locked, "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "all exits blocked, "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "help me, help me, help me, doc. "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "This room knows of many people, it "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "tells me every day, tells me of patient after "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "patient, 'these drugs that I'm taking' "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "that they want to get off, but their faces "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "say otherwise. "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "The patients here are mad, I see them bounce off the walls, "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Scream down the halls, armed with these strange "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "kinds of guns, knives and tools, I refuse "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "to admit them in for anything else, their general "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "health all sums up to schizophrenia. "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "I have written it so many times, that those keys "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "no longer function, I mean, "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "they're MAD, CRAZY, ALL INSANE, CIA "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "GLOWIES, how can I not sign "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "them up for this condition without proper diagnosis. "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "It's the CIA injecting weed into their DNA. "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "It's all caused by mitosis, even when they're "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "sitting there, silent, sad, I'm convinced that they're mad in catosis, "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "It used to make me green sick, but "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "now I'm desensitised; chlorosis. These schizos "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "dragging me out of my freaking ward, I scream \"Idiots\", \"Dumbasses\", \"Gores\" "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "On the other side of the door. "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 2
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Now they're tryna convict me for stuff without a reason "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "can the CIA not See? "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "Two years later on drugs, behind bars in prison, "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "I come to a revelation. "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 1
            },
            {
                "type": "text",
                "content": "The schizo was me. "
            },
            {
                "type": "newline",
                "count": 3
            }
        ]
    },
    "pageStyle": "poem-centre-wide",
    "pageBackground": ""
}